The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Ten persons, including four cops, were injured in Metiabruz on Tuesday night following a clash during immersion. Police said members of four clubs started throwing stones after they were told to take separate routes to the ghat.					  Fatal mishap: Brothers Sanjib Sarkar, 28, and Arup Sarkar, 32, were run over by a truck when the bike they were riding hit a divider on the EM Bypass near Ajoynagar on Wednesday night. Their brother Prasanta, who was also on the bike, was admitted to hospital in a critical condition.   Fire: Fire broke out in a chemical godown in Burrabazar on Wednesday. Four tenders doused the flames.   Injured: Four traffic cops were injured in two accidents on Wednesday. M. Rahman, 57, Swapan Sinha, 34, and Biswajit Pramanick, 20, were injured when a trailer hit their jeep near Vidyasagar Setu. In another incident, Sudipto Roy Chowdhury, 31, was injured when a taxi hit his motorcycle on Taratala Road.  Burglary: Burglars looted jewellery and cash worth over Rs 1 lakh from a Regent Park house late on Tuesday.  Drowned: Panchanan Baouli, a Bagbazar Street resident in his 70s, drowned while taking a dip in the Hooghly near Lockgate canal around noon on Wednesday.                                                                                                                                               
